            <i class="faq-toggle bi bi-chevron-right"></i>
          </div><!-- End Faq item-->

          <!-- FAQ Item 2: Referral Requirement -->
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Do I need a referral to see a specialist?</h3>
            <div class="faq-content">
              <p>No, a referral is not required to consult with our specialists. However, if you were referred by another doctor, please bring your medical records for a more accurate diagnosis and treatment plan.</p>
            </div>
            <i class="faq-toggle bi bi-chevron-right"></i>
          </div><!-- End Faq item-->

          <!-- FAQ Item 3: Insurance Plans -->
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What insurance plans do you accept?</h3>
            <div class="faq-content">
              <p>We accept a wide range of insurance providers. For a complete list, please visit our insurance page or contact our billing department. We also offer self-pay options for uninsured patients.</p>
            </div>
            <i class="faq-toggle bi bi-chevron-right"></i>
          </div><!-- End Faq item-->

          <!-- FAQ Item 4: What to Bring -->
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What should I bring to my first visit?</h3>
            <div class="faq-content">
              <p>Kindly bring a valid ID, any previous medical records, a list of current medications, and your insurance card (if applicable). Arriving 15 minutes early is also recommended for registration.</p>
            </div>
            <i class="faq-toggle bi bi-chevron-right"></i>
          </div><!-- End Faq item-->

